The curve below is called a \emph{lemniscate}; it is given by the
equation

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle (x^2 + y^2)^2 = 18(x^2 - y^2)
\end{align*}

Find the equation of the tangent line at the point $(2, \sqrt{2})$ and
sketch the tangent line.

